{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"multilineTextAlignment","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"alignment","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/TextAlignment","text":"TextAlignment","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore13TextAlignmentO"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A value that you use to align multiple lines of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text within a view."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"alignment"}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that aligns the lines of multiline ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" instances","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it contains.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier to set an alignment for a multiline block of text.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, the modifier centers the contents of the following","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"text":" view:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"This is a block of text that shows up in a text element as multiple lines.\\(\"\\n\") Here we have chosen to center this text.\")","    .frame(width: 200)","    .multilineTextAlignment(.center)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The text in the above example spans more than one line because:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The newline character introduces a line break."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The frame modifier limits the space available to the text view, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by default a text view wraps lines that don’t fit in the available","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"width. As a result, the text before the explicit line break wraps to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"three lines, and the text after uses two lines.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier applies the alignment to the all the lines of text in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the view, regardless of why wrapping occurs:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier has no effect on a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"text":" view that contains only one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"line of text, because a text view has a width that exactly matches the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"width of its widest line. If you want to align an entire text view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than its contents, set the aligment of its container, like a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack"},{"text":" or a frame that you create with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/frame(minWidth:idealWidth:maxWidth:minHeight:idealHeight:maxHeight:alignment:)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use this modifier to control the alignment of a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view that you create with the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text\/init(_:style:)"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to display localized dates and times, including when the view uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only a single line, but only when that view appears in a widget."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier also affects the content alignment of other text container","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types, like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TextEditor"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TextField"},{"text":". In those cases, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier sets the alignment even when the view contains only a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"line because view’s width isn’t dictated by the width of the text it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"contains.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The modifier operates by setting the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/EnvironmentValues\/multilineTextAlignment","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" value in the environment,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so it affects all the text containers in the modified view hierarchy."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, you can apply the modifier to a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configure all the text views inside the stack."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ButtonStyleConfiguration\/Label-swift.struct\/multilineTextAlignment(_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/View\/Text\/Util\/EnvironmentParagraphStyle.swift#L383","fileName":"EnvironmentParagraphStyle.swift"},"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","platforms":[{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"10.15"},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"6.0"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"multilineTextAlignment"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore13TextAlignmentO","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TextAlignment"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"precise